rgy Projects and Power Purchase Agreements + Coastal Virginia Offshore Wind + Renewable Energy Portfolio Standard\",\"fixedchargefirstmeter\":201.65,\"fixedchargeunits\":\"$/month\",\"country\":\"USA\"},{\"label\":\"69e99cf96746522c70079990\",\"uri\":\"https://apps.openei.org/IURDB/rate/view/69e99cf96746522c70079990\",\"revisions\":[1776896153,1776896827],\"approved\":true,\"is_default\":false,\"utility\":\"Virginia Electric & Power Co\",\"eiaid\":19876,\"name\":\"GS-4 (Large General Service Primary Voltage)\",\"startdate\":1767254400,\"supersedes\":\"69cec04f8497adf75202b22e\",\"sector\":\"Commercial\",\"servicetype\":\"Bundled\",\"description\":\"Except as modified herein, this schedule is applicable only to a non-residential transmission or primary voltage Customer (as defined in Paragraph XII.) (1) who elects (a) to receive Electricity Supply Service and Electric Delivery Service from the Company or (b) who is eligible for and elects to purchase Electricity Supply Service from a Competitive Service Provider in accordance with Va. Code &sect; 56-577A and (2) whose peak measured demand has reached or exceeded 500 kW during atleast three billing months within the current and previous 11 billing months.\",\"source\":\"https://cdn-dominionenergy-prd-001.azureedge.net/-/media/content/rates-and-tariffs/pdfs/virginia/large-business/schedule-gs4.pdf?rev=455480cb8074465f9f963ee9438d74bd&hash=8B4D0EF71C0AC4AB2E5775852FDF6EB1\",\"sourceparent\":\"https://www.dominionenergy.com/virginia/rates-and-tariffs/business-rates\",\"peakkwcapacitymin\":500,\"demandunits\":\"kW\",\"flatdemandunit\":\"kW\",\"demandrateunit\":\"kW\",\"demandratestructure\":[[{\"max\":5000,\"rate\":3.275,\"adj\":0.268},{\"rate\":2.634,\"adj\":0.268}],[{\"max\":5000,\"rate\":14.524,\"adj\":9.068},{\"rate\":13.883,\"adj\":9.068}]],\"demandreactivepowercharge\":0.393,\"demandratchetpercentage\":[0,0,0,0,0,0.75,0.75,0.75,0.75,0,0,0],\"demandcomments\":\"Rate = Distribution + Generation Energy Supply || \\r\\nAdjustments: \\r\\nRiders that apply to the monthly peak demand: DIST(0.229$/kW) + RBB(0.039$/kW) = $0.268/kW\\r\\nRiders that apply to the on-peak monthly demand: CERC(0.161$/kW) + E(0.147$/kW) + GEN(0.993$/kW) + SMR(0.069$/kW) + SNA(0.836$/kW) + T1(4.175$/kW) + (non-bypassable) CE(0.425$/kWh) + (non-bypassable) OSW(1.994$/kWh) = $8.8/kW\",\"energyratestructure\":[[{\"unit\":\"kWh\",\"rate\":0.003456,\"adj\":0.039759}],[{\"unit\":\"kWh\",\"rate\":0.004805,\"adj\":0.039759}]],\"energycomments\":\"Rate = Distribution + Generation + Transmission || Adjustments = A - fuel charge(0.02968$/kWh) + C1A - peak shaving(0.000095$/kWh) + C4A - energy efficiency(0.000543$/kWh) + (non-bypassable) CCR(0.001765$/kWh) + (non-bypassable) RPS(0.007676$/kWh) = $0.039759/kWh\",\"dgrules\":\"Net Metering\",\"fixedchargefirstmeter\":343.54,\"fixedchargeunits\":\"$/month\",\"country\":\"USA\"}]",
